members.name: _id
members.doc: ID of the order to mark as `ACCEPTED`.

members.name: message
members.doc: Optional message added during order activity.

members.name: addressLine
members.doc: Main address line, usually street and number, as free text.

members.name: addressLine2
members.doc:
Free text providing more detailed address information,
such as apartment, suite, or floor.

members.name: formattedAddress
members.doc:
Human-readable address string.
If not provided, the value is generated from the available address data.

members.name: hint
members.doc: Instructions to help someone find the address, such as landmarks or where the entrance is.

members.name: streetAddress
members.doc: Street address object, with number and name in separate fields.

members.name: subdivision
members.doc:
Code for a subdivision (such as state, prefecture, or province) in an
[ISO 3166-2](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-2) format.

members.name: subdivisions
members.doc: Hierarchical list of subdivisions, where the first array item is the highest level of hierarchy, and so on.

members.name: items
members.doc: List of site contributor user IDs.

members.name: search
members.doc: Plain text search for an exact match, up to 100 characters.

members.name: jobId
members.doc:
Bulk job ID.
The job's status can be retrieved with
[Get Bulk Job](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/contacts/contacts/bulk-jobs/get-bulk-job) or
[List Bulk Jobs](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/contacts/contacts/bulk-jobs/list-bulk-jobs).

members.name: filter
members.doc:
Filter options.
Labels will be removed from contacts that meet the `filter` and `search` criteria.

members.name: labelKeysToAdd
members.doc: List of label keys to add to the contacts.

members.name: labelKeysToRemove
members.doc: List of label keys to remove from the contacts.

members.name: search
members.doc:
Plain text search for an exact match, up to 100 characters.
Labels will be removed from contacts that meet the `filter` and `search` criteria.

members.name: jobId
members.doc:
Bulk job ID.
The job's status can be retrieved with
[Get Bulk Job](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/contacts/contacts/bulk-jobs/get-bulk-job) or
[List Bulk Jobs](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/contacts/contacts/bulk-jobs/list-bulk-jobs).

members.name: fieldMask
members.doc:
Set of fields to update.
Fields that aren't included in `fieldMask.paths` are ignored.
See
[Field Masks in Update Requests](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/contacts/contacts/field-masks-in-update-requests)
for details on working with field masks.

members.name: search
members.doc: Plain text search for an exact match, up to 100 characters.

members.name: jobId
members.doc:
Bulk job ID.
The job's status can be retrieved with
[Get Bulk Job](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/contacts/contacts/bulk-jobs/get-bulk-job) or
[List Bulk Jobs](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/contacts/contacts/bulk-jobs/list-bulk-jobs).

members.name: _id
members.doc: ID of the order to mark as `CANCELED`.

members.name: catalogItemDescription
members.doc: Item description as defined in the catalog.

members.name: catalogItemId
members.doc: Line item ID as defined in the catalog.

members.name: catalogItemMedia
members.doc: Item media url as defined in the catalog.

members.name: catalogItemName
members.doc: Line item name as defined in the catalog.

members.name: _createdDate
members.doc: Date and time the contact was created.

members.name: _updatedDate
members.doc: Date and time the contact was last updated.

members.name: lastActivity
members.doc: Details about the contact's last action in the site.

members.name: picture
members.doc:
Contact's profile picture.
This can contain an image URL and a Wix Media image ID.

members.name: revision
members.doc:
Revision number, which increments by 1 each time the contact is updated.
To prevent conflicting changes,
the existing `revision` must be used when updating a contact.

members.name: activityDate
members.doc: Date and time of the last action.

members.name: activityType
members.doc: Contact's last action in the site.

members.name: tag
members.doc:
Address type.
`UNTAGGED` is shown as "Other" in the Contact List.

members.name: primary
members.doc:
Indicates whether this is the contact's primary email address.
When changing `primary` to `true` for an email,
the contact's other emails become `false`.

members.name: items
members.doc: List of up to 50 email addresses.

members.name: assignedUserIds
members.doc:
Site contributors
who are assigned to manage communication with the contact.

members.name: extendedFields
members.doc:
Additional custom fields.
This includes fields managed by Wix, by 3rd-party apps, and by the site.

members.name: jobTitle
members.doc:
Contact's job title.
Corresponds to the **Position** field in the Dashboard.

members.name: labelKeys
members.doc:
List of contact's labels.
Labels are used to organize contacts.
When setting the `labelKeys` property,
only labels that already exist in the site's Contacts List can be used.
Labels can be added and removed using
[Label Contact](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/contacts/contacts/contacts-v4/label-contact) and
[Unlabel Contact](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/contacts/contacts/contacts-v4/unlabel-contact),
respectively.

members.name: locale
members.doc:
Contact's locale, formatted as an
[IETF BCP 47 language tag](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5646).
Typically, this is a lowercase 2-letter language code,
followed by a hyphen,
followed by an uppercase 2-letter country code.

members.name: sourceContactIds
members.doc: IDs of contacts there were merged into the target contact.

members.name: e164Phone
members.doc:
[ITU E.164-formatted](https://www.itu.int/rec/T-REC-E.164/)
phone number.
Automatically generated using `phone` and `countryCode`,
as long as both of those values are valid.

members.name: formattedPhone
members.doc:
Human-readable phone number.
Automatically generated using `phone` and `countryCode`,
as long as both of those values are valid.

members.name: primary
members.doc:
Whether this is the contact's primary phone number.
When changing `primary` to `true` for a phone,
the contact's other phones become `false`.

members.name: items
members.doc: List of up to 50 phone numbers.

members.name: image
members.doc:
Image.
This can contain an image URL or a Wix Media image ID.

members.name: imageProvider
members.doc:
Indicates whether the image is retrieved from Wix Media
or an external provider.

members.name: appId
members.doc: App ID, if the contact was created by an app.

members.name: wixAppId
members.doc: App ID, if the contact was created by a Wix app.

members.name: passThroughData
members.doc: Pass through data, submitted with the contact

members.name: count
members.doc: Number of contacts the facet is applied to.

members.name: facetDisplayName
members.doc: Human-readable name. Shown in the Wix UI.

members.name: legacyId
members.doc: Legacy ID of the facet label

members.name: namespace
members.doc:
Scope for facet keys.
When a facet key exists in a namespace,
each key is unique within that namespace.

members.name: queryFilter
members.doc: Filter used for query contacts of this facet

members.name: allowDuplicates
members.doc:
Controls whether the call will succeed
if the new contact information contains an email already used by another contact.

members.name: cursor
members.doc: Cursor returned in last query response. Should not be provided on first page request

members.name: limit
members.doc: The number of contacts to load (default = 50, max = 1000)

members.name: next
members.doc: Cursor pointing to next result page

members.name: prev
members.doc: Cursor pointing to previous result page

members.name: contactId
members.doc:
Customer's contact ID.
See [Contacts API](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/contacts/contacts/contacts-v4) for more details.

members.name: contactId
members.doc: ID of the contact to delete.

members.name: approximate
members.doc: Whether an approximate address is used. Defaults to `false`. In case of `false` a house number is required.

members.name: comment
members.doc: Delivery Instructions added by the customer.

members.name: onArrival
members.doc: Special delivery instructions upon arrival to the address.

members.name: subdivision
members.doc: Subdivision. Usually a state, region, prefecture, or province code, according to [ISO 3166-2](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-2).

members.name: label
members.doc: Label of dine-in information added by the restaurant, e.g. `table` or `booth`.

members.name: value
members.doc: Value of dine-in information added by the restaurant, e.g. `#6`.

members.name: catalogDiscountId
members.doc: Discount ID as defined in the catalog.

members.name: catalogDiscountName
members.doc: Discount name as defined in the catalog.

members.name: items
members.doc:
Contact's extended fields,
where each key is the field key,
and each value is the field's value for the contact.

members.name: _id
members.doc: ID of the external delivery provider.

members.name: commission
members.doc: Fee paid by the restuarant to the external delivery provider.

members.name: customerFee
members.doc: Delivery fee charged to the customer.

members.name: name
members.doc: Name of the external delivery provider.

members.name: _id
members.doc: ID of the order to mark as `FULFILLED`.

members.name: asap
members.doc: Whether the order should be fulfilled as soon as possible. Defaults to `true`.

members.name: promisedTime
members.doc: Latest delivery time promised by the restaurant.

members.name: contactId
members.doc: ID of the contact whose picture is being updated.

members.name: mimeType
members.doc:
Mime Type. Must be one of:
`image/png`, `image/jpeg`.
Defaults to `image/png`.

members.name: minChoices

members.name: lineItems
